{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Arithmetic and spelling, and all of that-- I was much, much ahead of the French children when I got back to school in Paris.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was eight years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the life-- the life of a French Jewish girl, I think I'm typical.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, we are French since the 17th century, and didn't have very much to do with the people who immigrated from-- from Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all we knew was about our life and I can't say that I ever-- ever was exposed to anti-Semitism, or-- never in my time and never-- it never happened to me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was saying before that, since the Dreyfus affair, I think that my-- my youth happened to be following the Dreyfus affair.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the French were pretty ashamed of what happened during Dreyfus, and I think that we benefited from that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that might be one reason why I never-- I never knew any anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, my God-- I hope everybody remembers that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was Captain Dreyfus who was denounced as being a spy in the French army, and was denounced by a man by the name of Esterhazy.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was going to be, I expect, killed or in prison for life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Emile Zola, the famous writer, had enough courage to write something very, very well-known called, where he is accusing the French government and the military for having-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for having tried to-- to convict a man who wasn't-- who was innocent.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was finally-- he was finally rehabilitated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was something that the French-- the French felt quite ashamed about it, because it involved the whole French people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, everybody was anti-Dreyfus.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't say-- I don't say I felt a feeling of shame.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
